mimosa-assistant (2.0.0~beta-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Polish sprint (v2.0.0-beta): 12 UX and robustness fixes on top of the
    v2.0.0-alpha avatar system.
  * New-install avatar defaults: fresh installs now enable the avatar with a
    hardware-detected tier; upgraders keep the classic listening circle
    (avatar.enabled=false) for backward compatibility.
  * Setup wizard: new "Your Avatar" preset picker (feminine/masculine/neutral
    /circle) with paired voice defaults, a "Your Voice" step with voice
    dropdown and ▶ Play Sample audition button, and clearer step titles.
  * Settings: new Avatar tab (enable, tier, voice, animation speed) with a
    Play Sample button.
  * Robustness: graceful degradation with no audio / no GTK / no GPU; audio
    error-spam suppressed; clearer capability-detection and startup
    visualization logging.
  * Performance: opt-in avatar frame-rate governor (auto-throttle) that lowers
    FPS then falls back to the circle under sustained load.
  * Documentation: README "What's New in v2.0" section and docs/UPGRADING.md
    (v1.1.0 → v2.0.0) migration guide.
  * Testing: new integration tests (avatar pipeline, setup-to-launch) and
    frame-rate governor unit tests.

