mimosa-assistant (2.0.0~alpha-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Phase 8 / v2.0.0-alpha: The Avatar System — MimOSA gains a customizable
    2D character avatar with emotions, lip sync, and gestures.
  * Milestone 8.1 (Infrastructure): Avatar module with BaseAvatarRenderer and
    Sprite2DRenderer, hardware capability detection (none/basic_2d/advanced_2d
    /full_3d tiers), AvatarSettings configuration, AvatarCharacterWindow GTK4
    transparent overlay.
  * Milestone 8.2 (Generation): AI-powered avatar generation with Stable
    Diffusion fallback, three hand-crafted SVG default avatars (feminine,
    masculine, neutral), sprite processor with PIL/Pillow pipeline, cache
    manager with automatic cleanup, preview dialog integrated into wizard.
  * Milestone 8.3 (Animation): 6 emotion states (idle, listening, thinking,
    speaking, happy, concerned), unified animator state machine with smooth
    transitions, 8 phoneme-mapped mouth shapes (visemes), real-time lip sync
    engine synchronized with TTS, 6 gesture animations (wave, thinking,
    explaining, thumbs_up, shrug, point) with priority-based interpolation.
  * Milestone 8.4 (Voice Integration): Expanded to 20 Piper voices with rich
    metadata, voice auditioner backend, speech callback system with automatic
    duration estimation, full pipeline: voice loop → GTK main thread →
    renderer → animator → lip sync → animated mouth shapes.
  * Documentation: Complete 505-line AVATAR_SYSTEM.md guide with features,
    configuration, migration guide (v1.1.0 → v2.0.0-alpha), technical
    architecture, performance benchmarks, troubleshooting, API reference.
  * Technical: 13 new avatar modules (~5,400 lines), 114 new tests (1,782
    total), 60 FPS on modern hardware / 30 FPS on low-end.
  * Backward compatible: avatar.enabled defaults to false for existing users
    (opt-in), preserving classic listening circle. New users get avatars by
    default.
  * Deferred to v2.1.0: Setup wizard voice+avatar selection UI, Settings
    avatar tab, visual voice audition dialog (backends complete, UI polish
    follows).

