mimosa-assistant (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Milestone 4: Continuous Learning & Polish — MimOSA grows from a one-time
    learner into a companion that keeps getting to know you over time.
  * Continuous learning: facts and preferences are now picked up from everyday
    conversations (not just onboarding) and folded into your local profile.
  * Proactive questions: MimOSA may occasionally ask a thoughtful "get to know
    you" question, gently rate-limited to one or two a day and fully opt-out.
  * Memory consolidation: duplicate memories are merged, contradictions are
    reconciled and stale clutter is tidied, so memory stays accurate and lean.
  * Relationship tracking: MimOSA understands how well it knows you (new →
    familiar → close) and adjusts its warmth and familiarity accordingly.
  * Context-aware suggestions: high-confidence, time/pattern-aware nudges
    ("you usually start coding around now…") that you can switch off any time.
  * New Settings: Learning Preferences (questions, frequency, suggestions,
    learn-from-conversations), Memory Management (view memory, consolidate)
    and a friendly display of your current relationship stage.
  * Conversation quality: light emotion awareness and reference resolution so
    follow-ups like "open it again" feel natural.
  * Everything stays local-only and opt-out; learning never gates core
    functionality and never interrupts a conversation.

 -- ServiceFly <info.markethiveapp@gmail.com>  Sat, 13 Jun 2026 01:59:44 +0000

mimosa-assistant (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Milestone 3: conversational onboarding & memory system — MimOSA's first
    full release. After setup, MimOSA can have a warm, friend-like "get to
    know you" chat (never a dry questionnaire) and remembers what it learns.
  * New on-device memory store (Chroma-backed with a pure-Python fallback)
    holding four collections: user profile, conversation history, learned
    preferences and episodic memories — all stored locally under
    ~/.local/share/mimosa/memory.
  * Adaptive conversation engine across seven topics with follow-up
    questions, response-depth analysis and gentle encouragement for thin
    answers; pause/resume so an interrupted onboarding picks up where it
    left off.
  * LLM-assisted fact extraction (with a heuristic offline fallback) builds
    a structured user profile that is injected into the assistant's system
    prompt so answers feel personal.
  * Settings gains "Review / Edit My Profile", "Redo Onboarding" and
    "Clear All Memories".
  * Graceful degradation throughout: missing Chroma falls back to JSON, a
    missing LLM falls back to heuristic extraction, and onboarding is
    always optional and resumable.

 -- ServiceFly <info.markethiveapp@gmail.com>  Sat, 13 Jun 2026 01:20:27 +0000

mimosa-assistant (1.0.0~rc3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Milestone 2: custom wake-word training system. Train a personal wake
    word (e.g. "Jarvis") entirely on-device — no audio ever leaves your
    machine, and "Hey MimOSA" always remains as a guaranteed fallback.
  * Setup wizard redesigned with a persistent, friendly guidance sidebar
    (replacing the old per-field info-icon tooltips) and a new "Your Own
    Wake Word" step with live name analysis (difficulty, success odds,
    phonetics, false-trigger warnings and per-hardware time estimates).
  * New training UI with staged progress, time remaining, pause/resume and
    cancel; a "Test Your Wake Word" step; and a one-time dependency
    download prompt before pulling the ~2.5 GB training stack.
  * Gender-aware Piper voice selection for synthetic training data and
    spoken responses.
  * Settings gains "Re-run Setup Wizard" and "Train a custom wake word"
    actions (other settings are preserved).
  * Graceful degradation throughout: training never crashes the assistant
    and always falls back to "Hey MimOSA".

