mimosa-assistant (1.0.0~rc2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Milestone 1: replaced Porcupine with openWakeWord for 100% local,
    key-free wake-word detection.
  * Fixed config persistence (settings.json always written on first run).
  * Added a consistent MimOSA identity and a warm, natural conversational
    tone across all LLM-backed skills.
  * install.sh now installs a "mimosa" launcher on PATH (~/.local/bin).
  * Settings: microphone/speaker pickers are now dropdowns of detected
    devices instead of free-text fields.
  * Added silent on-device hardware-capability detection (for future
    on-device wake-word training) and a voice-style (gender) preference.

